members.name: test
members.comment: Evaluates this predicate on the given argument.

return: true if the input argument matches the predicate, otherwise false

members.name: and
members.comment: Returns a composed predicate that represents a short-circuiting logical AND of this predicate and another. When evaluating the composed predicate, if this predicate is false, then the other predicate is not evaluated. Any exceptions thrown during evaluation of either predicate are relayed to the caller; if evaluation of this predicate throws an exception, the other predicate will not be evaluated.

param: other - a predicate that will be logically-ANDed with this predicate
throws: NullPointerException - if other is null
return: a composed predicate that represents the short-circuiting logical AND of this predicate and the other predicate

members.name: negate
members.comment: Returns a predicate that represents the logical negation of this predicate.

return: a predicate that represents the logical negation of this predicate

members.name: or
members.comment: Returns a composed predicate that represents a short-circuiting logical OR of this predicate and another. When evaluating the composed predicate, if this predicate is true, then the other predicate is not evaluated. Any exceptions thrown during evaluation of either predicate are relayed to the caller; if evaluation of this predicate throws an exception, the other predicate will not be evaluated.

param: other - a predicate that will be logically-ORed with this predicate
throws: NullPointerException - if other is null
return: a composed predicate that represents the short-circuiting logical OR of this predicate and the other predicate

name: java.util.function.LongPredicate
comment:
Represents a predicate (boolean-valued function) of one long-valued argument. This is the long-consuming primitive type specialization of Predicate.

This is a functional interface whose functional method is test(long).
